addModule(string,string,address).details: Adds a module to the contract with the given ModuleName and Version on the given ModuleAddress.

allowance(address,address).details: Retrieves the Allowance of the given Spender address in the given Owner wallet.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approves the given amount for the given Spender address in the Message Sender wallet.

balanceInPlayerPool(address).details: Retrieve the balance of a player from the player pool.

balanceOf(address).details: Retrieves the Balance Of the given address. Note: If the address is included in the Reward process, retrieves the Token equivalent of the held Reward amount.

decimals().details: Retrieves the Number of Decimal Points of the token.

excludeFromFee(address).details: Excludes an address from the Fee process.

excludeFromReward(address).details: Excludes an address from the Reward process.

getModule(string).details: Retrieves a 2-tuple (success? + search result) by the given ModuleName.

getOwner().details: Retrieves the Owner of the token.

includeInFee(address).details: Includes an address in the Fee process.

includeInReward(address).details: Includes an address in the Reward process.

isExcludedFromFee(address).details: Retrieves if the given address is excluded from the Fee process.

isExcludedFromReward(address).details: Retrieves if the given address is excluded from the Reward process.

name().details: Retrieves the Name of the Token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ping().details: Occasionally called (only) by the server to make sure that the connection with the contract is granted.

previousOwner().details: Returns the address of the previous owner.

removeModule(string).details: Removes a module from the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without an owner. It won't be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.

rewardFromToken(uint256,bool).details: Retrieves the Reward equivalent of the given Token amount. (With the Fees optionally included or excluded.)

setBitDuelServiceFeePercent(uint256).details: Sets the BitDuel Service Fee percentage.

setDevWallet(address).details: Sets the given address as the Developer Wallet.

setMaxTxPercent(uint256).details: Sets the maximum transaction amount. (calculated by the given percentage)

setPancakeSwapPair(address).details: Sets the given address as the Pancake Swap Pair.

setPancakeSwapRouter(address).details: Sets the given address as the Pancake Swap Router.

setPlayerBalance(address,uint256).details: Called by BitDuel after a won / lost game, to set the new balance of a user in the player pool. The gas price is provided by BitDuel.

setPlayerPoolWallet(address).details: Sets the given address as the Player Pool Hot Wallet.

symbol().details: Retrieves the Symbol of the token.

tokenFromReward(uint256).details: Retrieves the Token equivalent of the given Reward amount.

totalBitDuelServiceFees().details: Retrieves the Total BitDuel Service Fees deducted to date.

totalDevelopmentFees().details: Retrieves the Total Development Fees deducted to date.

totalEventFees().details: Retrieves the Total Event Fees deducted to date.

totalFees().details: Retrieves the Total Fees deducted to date.

totalMarketingFees().details: Retrieves the Total Marketing Fees deducted to date.

totalSupply().details: Retrieves the Total Supply of the token.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfers the given Amount of tokens (minus the fees, if any) from the Message Senders wallet to the Recipients wallet. Note: If the Recipient is the Player Pool Hot Wallet, the Message Sender will be able to play with the transferred amount of Tokens on BitDuel.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers the given Amount of tokens from the Sender to the Recipient address if the Sender approved on the Message Sender allowances.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(uint256).details: A function used to withdraw from the player pool.
